Rooms, services and location (center of city and near all tourist places) all are excellent. Very helpful staff. I had a pleasant stay. The helpful staff and service was only because I paid a unreasonably high amount.

But they overcharged. I paid Rs 3000 for 2 rooms for many days. But even the online vendors offer the rooms at lesser amount. And I went to him offline directly. But they actually billed more than real prices. This is just wrong. I later also found cheaper rooms empty in the same hotel but they refused to give me those.

I had old parents with me and I could not put them through much movement. So I continued. But as I found out the real prices and the empty available rooms I realised they completely took advantage of me. They did not even get me room with windows when I waited for days and those rooms were available but they kept saying they are booked even after paying this hefty sum.

You should avoid this hotel as an Indian because you cannot compete with the unreasonable amounts foreigners can pay. This hotel has 90% foreign travellers. If you still need to stay, you should not pay more than Rs 2000 for this property. This I am quoting when online portals even give this hotel at Rs 1600 for deluxe rooms. And from my own extensive travel experience in Rajasthan and India regularly.

I wanted to give this hotel 5 stars but this experience left me feeling cheated very badly.

And do not approach them for any cab service or any shopping help. They will point you to contacts that give them commision and hence those cabs or shops or services loot you.

Overall, the staffing was quite attentive, the service was good, and the rooms were clean. Despite the few drawbacks, I recommend Hotel V Inn for visitors looking for a decent place to stay in Jaipur.

The hotel is conveniently located in the heart of Jaipur, making it easy to explore major attractions like Hawa Mahal, City Palace, and Johri Bazaar. Public transport and cab services are easily available, which made our sightseeing hassle-free.

Our stay at Hotel Metro Regency was delightful, and we highly recommend it to female travelers, families, and anyone looking for a comfortable stay in Jaipur. The excellent hospitality, cleanliness, and security make it a great choice for tourists.

I recently stayed at Fab Bohra International for a weekend getaway, and overall, it was a pleasant experience. The hotel is conveniently located just a short walk from the main train station, making it an ideal choice for travelers who want easy access to public transport. This proximity allowed me to explore the city effortlessly, which was a significant plus.

Upon arrival, I was greeted by the friendly front desk staff who made the check-in process smooth and efficient. Throughout my stay, the service remained consistently good. The staff was attentive and always willing to help with any questions or requests I had, whether it was providing directions or recommending local dining options.

One aspect that I found a bit disappointing was the lack of a complimentary breakfast. In this day and age, many hotels offer at least a basic breakfast included in the room rate, so it was surprising that The Fab did not. However, there are plenty of nearby cafes and eateries where you can grab a bite to eat, so it wasn’t a dealbreaker for me.

The room itself was comfortable and well-appointed, with modern amenities and a cozy atmosphere. I appreciated the cleanliness and attention to detail in the room’s decor. The bed was particularly comfortable, ensuring that I had restful nights after long days of exploring.
I would definitely return on my next visit!

Hotel Metro Regency, Jaipur – A Safe & Comfortable Stay for Female Travelers

During our recent trip to Jaipur, we stayed at Hotel Metro Regency, and we couldn’t be happier with our experience. As female travelers, safety and comfort were our top priorities, and this hotel exceeded our expectations in every way.

Location & Accessibility

The hotel is conveniently located in the heart of Jaipur, making it easy to explore major attractions like Hawa Mahal, City Palace, and Johri Bazaar. Public transport and cab services are easily available, which made our sightseeing hassle-free.

Hospitality & Service

From the moment we checked in, the hotel staff made us feel extremely welcome. The check-in process was smooth, and the reception staff was friendly and accommodating. They ensured that we had all the necessary information about the hotel’s facilities and even offered assistance with local travel tips.

The housekeeping and room service teams were prompt and efficient. The hotel staff showed great professionalism, which made us feel secure and valued as guests.

Rooms & Cleanliness

The rooms were spacious, clean, and well-maintained. The bedding was fresh, and the room had all essential amenities like air conditioning, a TV, and complimentary WiFi. The washrooms were spotless, with 24-hour hot water availability. We truly appreciated the attention to hygiene and cleanliness.

Food & Dining

The hotel offers an in-house restaurant with a variety of dishes, and the food quality was excellent. The breakfast was delicious and had a good mix of Indian and continental options. The staff was courteous and ensured that our dining experience was pleasant.

Safety & Comfort for Female Travelers

One of the best aspects of Hotel Metro Regency is how safe and secure it felt for female travelers. The hotel has round-the-clock security, and the staff was respectful and attentive, ensuring that we felt comfortable throughout our stay.

Overall Experience

Our stay at Hotel Metro Regency was delightful, and we highly recommend it to female travelers, families, and anyone looking for a comfortable stay in Jaipur. The excellent hospitality, cleanliness, and security make it a great choice for tourists.

Rating: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5)
Would definitely stay here again on our next visit to Jaipur!
